<br>
This continues a myth that was never so.<br>
<br>
Monks have always been good tanks. Pre-Kunark, during Kunark, in Vellious and in SoL.<br>
<br>
It is not something we have to apologise for. We have always (since Rogues were rijigged) done less damage than the Rogue and more than the Warrior, and tanked better than the Rogue but not as well as the Warrior.<br>
<br>
It is the last part that is failing, not because there is something wrong with Monks, but because there is something Wrong with the way in Warrior abilities are capped (everybodies actually).<br>
<br>
We do not have to apologies for being able to tank.<br>
<br>
We do not have to get into comparisons with Hybrids over melee prowess... WE are the pure melees, we balance with the other pure melees, and then Hybrids are related to that.... They are PART Warrior, and part their &quot;parent&quot; class.<br>
<br>
The reasoning of the problem is simple lets not confuse it.<br>
<br>
The issue of balance is among the pure melees, do not let the Knights muddy the issue.<br>
<br>
Warriors, Monks, Rogues... we balance those three FIRST... then we worry about relating the Hybrids to that.... if not we got a bunch of Tank Mages running around. <p><hr />
