n due to poor design.<br>
<br>
The items are the problem.  They can fix them a number of ways.  Raise their weight (and a PSC at 5 isn't that limiting.  Lots of monks use Tstaves still...).  Reduce their stats.  Change who can use them.  I think all of those are valid ways of addressing the issue, and depending on the item a different fix would be called for (ancient wyvern hide armor is a good example of something that should be made monk-only and have its stats lowered).<br>
<br>
I know a lot of monks wouldn't like this change.  I wouldn't, many of my items would become nerfed or unusable.  However I feel that this is a better solution than gimping us on a combat table, one that will ALWAYS gimp us.  Fixing these items is a short term nerf; in the long run we'll be just fine.<br>
<br>
Regardless, please don't take this so personally.  Obviously many people have different opinions, and some folks share mine and some folks share yours.  Let's not have it be something to be hostile over.<br>
